history.text: Hello!
Hi! The movie is Wonder Woman!
OK, yes I watched that opening weekend.
I still haven't seen it haha.
But I love Gal Gadot!
Yeah, she was a different kind of wonder woman from the original TV show.
I heard the original made a cameo, but I could be wrong
I wasn't expecting a foreign accent. I honestly don't remember if she made an appearance.
If she did, it was a small cameo I guess.
She's from Israel!
Wasn't expecting the movie to go into Greek Mythology too.. kinda cool to tie that in with the DC universe
Yeah I can't wait to watch it when I have a spare few hours LOL.
It was given a 92% approval rating on Rotten Tomatoes, which I guess is good
Overall it was well received, and critics thought it was better than the other DC movies.
I tend to disagree though and liked Man of Steel and Justice League.
Yeah it looks really good, possibly better than Man of Steel.
Wonder woman takes place way in the past and im not a big fan of movies from that setting.
But the whole movie isnt in that time, so I guess that helped.
yeah that's what I'm reading lol. I prefer present day, also
Plus the casting for the villian was god awful.. felt like a joke really
But Chris Pine, though.
People in the theater (including myself) laughed when we saw some parts that probably weren't mean to be funny.
I'll have to grab my popcorn and Reeses before I watch it. I tend to laugh at stuff that shouldn't be laughed at, also
Oh yeah you'll get a kick out of some things then.. im like, is this even trying to be a serious movie?
Are you into other super hero movies in the DC universe?
Yeah, I've seen them all so far I believe.
You?
Yeah a few. I'm not so keen on Batman.
Yeah, I have mixed feelings about that too.
I don't think that they should have even made a Batman v Superman movie. Honestly, Batman shouldn't even have had a chance
But Wonder Woman seems like a really good movie, it's just hard to watch it when I have a 3 year old running around
Oh yeah, I know all about the sacrifices made for our kids!
Do you watch movies even if they get a bad review?
Fortunatly, my parents are involved in my little girl's lives and relish the opportunity to spend time with them.
Yeah, definitely. If I liked the preview to something, I'll go see it regardless of how it was reviewed.
I just care about the reviews on movies that I was on the fence about.
My husband will too. He doesn't care
OK Well I think I'll wrap things up here.. was nice talking to you!

uid1response.feedback: I felt that this person was responding quite often to me and we didnt have any sticking points in the conversation.
